Tom Hanks Explains Why He’s Moving to Sidney, Ohio – WM21 News
SIDNEY, Ohio – In a huge surprise to everyone in Los Angeles, Hollywood actor Tom Hanks reveals in a new interview that he is moving to the Sidney, Ohio area. Hanks tells the magazine that he is “tired of the L.A. lifestyle” and is looking for a big change in life.

“I’m just tired of the L.A. lifestyle and I feel like, at this point in my life, I’d rather just live in a place full of real, genuine people. I’ve been to Sidney, Ohio a couple of times over the years and the people there are real… they’re genuine, and yeah every community has its problems but the people there are good, decent people and they care about their community. Those are the things I find most important in deciding where to live,” Hanks told the magazine.

“I’m not retiring, I’m just looking for a change in life and I think I’ve found that in Sidney,” Hanks reassured fans. Let us know what you think in the comments section especially if you’re a resident of the Sidney, Ohio area and click the share button above to share with friends.